text: Adams County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. As of the 2020 census, the population was 31,205. Its county seat is Hastings. The county was formed in 1867 and organized in 1871. It is named for John Adams, the second President of the United States. == References == == Other websites == * Adams County Website * Adams County Historical Society * Adams County Convention & Visitors Bureau Category:1871 establishments in Nebraska Category:Nebraska counties
